# SAP Explorer - Implementation & Architecture Plan

This document serves as the master blueprint for the **SAP Explorer** project. You can paste this document into the new `SAP Explorer` folder and provide it to the AI in your next session to immediately begin execution.

## 1. Project Goal & Scope
SAP Explorer is a purpose-built companion application to ARIA-CRM. 
**Primary Purpose:** To establish a communication bridge with SAP systems, allowing users to extract, map, and explore SAP BAPIs, Tables, and Logical Databases. This extracted intelligence will subsequently be utilized by ARIA-CRM.
**Aesthetics:** The application must exactly match the premium, dynamic, glassmorphic UI of ARIA-CRM, ensuring a seamless user experience across the Compass suite.

## 2. Technical Stack
- **Core Framework**: Next.js (App Router)
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4
- **UI & Animations**: Framer Motion, Lucide React
- **Backend & Auth (If required standalone)**: Prisma, Clerk

---

## 3. Session 1: Workspace Scaffolding
*In your new session, instruct the AI to execute these initialization steps.*

### Initialize Next.js
Run the following in the `C:\Users\baska\OneDrive\Documents\Compass\SAP Explorer` terminal:
```powershell
npx create-next-app@latest . --typescript --tailwind --eslint --app --src-dir --import-alias "@/*" --use-npm
```

### Install Core Dependencies
```powershell
npm install framer-motion lucide-react clsx tailwind-merge
npm install @clerk/nextjs @prisma/client
npm install prisma --save-dev
```

